                                         CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a culpable homicide case after two people were killed when two vehicles collided at a four-way stop in Hartswater. The collision on Thursday caused the double cab bakkie to roll into two men who were sitting nearby. The men died on the scene while the driver was transported to the hospital. The police's Sergio Kock said: “The investigation is currently continuing, the Athlone police also support the Arrive Alive campaign and therefore we request that motorists please during December and the festive season and beyond, please adhere to the road rules.”